        The role of "Principal" is far more than project management.
		At Nevo, our Principal's are the primary interface between
		the client and the project team.  We expect them to have the
		same level of technical ability as a Team Lead, but with greater
		management responsibility, often extending into budget planning,
		project management, executive level communication and more.
   <p>
   		We believe strongly that projects succeed or fail in the
   		requirements gathering phase, and we rely heavily on our
   		Principals to ensure that we "get the right requirements
   		and get the requirements right."

   <p>As a Principal you should have:

   <ul class="listText">
   		<li>Extensive professional experience
   		</li><li>Strong technical skills and demonstrated accomplishments
   		</li><li>Outstanding communications skills
   		</li><li>Deep understanding of what it takes to get projects done on time and on    		budget.  This starts with experience in project management.
   		</li><li>Demonstrated success in requirements gathering.  Doing this phase of the project right requires a combination of technical and interpersonal skills.
   </ul>

